Cloudy- damp- 60 F- mod. E wind
Rainy/cool most of a.m.- now 65 F- W breeze- 50% clouds
Rain last p.m.- this a.m.- strong W wind- overcast- 55 F- feels cold
Partly sunny- calm- 50% clouds- 60 F- slight. E breeze
Overcast- 50 F- brisk NE wind- water choppy
Sunny- 60 F- slight. N wind- rain early a.m.
Overcast- brisk S wind- water 40 F- air 34 F- snow yesterday
Few clouds- S wind- 60 F- whitecaps
Rain and wind during last 24 hours- cloudy- east wind- 60 F
Becoming weedy- sunny and calm all week- 70 F- east breeze- 50% cloud cover
Rained 2" overnight- cool- cloudy- windy (northwest) - 55 F
Overcast- rain this morning- northeast wind- 68 F
Early morning rain- overcast- slight breeze from e- cloudy- muggy- 85 F
Clear- 70 F- slight breeze from northeast
Northeast wind- choppy- 50% cloud cover- 75 F
Rain all am- slight breeze from e- 70 F- cloudy
Rained most of day- thick dark clouds- 65 F- choppy- e wind
N breeze- 90 F- clear- hot lately w/high humidity
Slight breeze- 74 F- some clouds- green spots in water- nice day
Sunny- 50 F- slight breeze from w
Partly cloudy- northwest wind- 58 F- pleasant day
Cloudy- 40 F- northwest wind- most weeds brown
100% clouds- heavy mist- 40 F- slight breeze.
Slight west breeze- hot and dry- weeds are growing.
Finally got some rain.  Noticed first algal blooms of the season.
Slight southern breeze- clear sky.  It has been rainy and cold every day for over a month.  First decent day to do the secchi reading.
Lots of algae- water really brown.
Water is choppy- cool northwest wind.  Rain predicted.
Cool- 60 degrees- 35 degrees the last two nights.  Wind is from the east.
South wind- choppy water - high humidity- 80 degrees- hazy sky.
Northern wind- 60 degrees- 100% cloud cover- rain storm sat- rained all day sun.
Breezy west wind- 40 degrees- cloud cover.
South strong wind- 65 degrees- clear sky.
West wind- no clouds- 70 degrees- a diamond day!
Windy from west- rained 5 days last week- 50 degrees and sunny- 40% cloud cover.
West wind- hazy sky- snowed 10/15- 45 degrees.
Northwest breeze- clear sky- 68 degrees- Indian summer- last test until next May.
No secchi depth reading on card
Some algae blooms- windy and temp is 38 degrees- the reason for samples taken on this day drawdown on lake to start 10/1//93
Ice off- water high after refilling the lake from the draw down.
Weather was warm.  Rain off + on most of the day.
Water lilies in bloom- beautiful weather- 68 degrees- sunny and slight NW wind. rain gauge 4.5 in. 6/01- 6/21.
Cloudy and the temperature is 78 degrees.  Puffy green algae clouds under water.
Water lilies in bloom in bays- water is choppy- southwest wind- and 4.75 inches of rain on 6/21-7/18.
Cloudy- windy- 75 degrees- thunderstorms in a.m.
Very windy- cloudy and in the 60s.
Hazy- 78 degrees- slight wind- sunny- green algae in the water.
Warm and 70's- sunny- 4th day of the flood water up about 6-7 ft.  The water should go down soon.
Cloudy- east wind- air temp is 45 degrees- last sample of 94 season- 15 inches of rain in 2 days- resulting in Phillips flood
Sunny morning- 65 degrees- rain off and on- cloudy the rest of the day- light breeze.
Ice off 4/20/95- wind and waves up 10 mph at time of the sample- overcast and 55 degrees.
70 degrees- partly sunny + breezy- rain the night before.
Pollen from pine trees is abundant- sunshine- temp is 68 degrees- wind is light southwest.
90 degrees- hot + humid.  Not a cloud in the sky- very light breeze.
80 degrees- partly cloudy- rained most of last night.
Twelve days above 90 degrees in the last 3 weeks- today temp is 60 degrees- lake level is normal- slight wind - NW wind- bright sunshine.
80's- sunshine- light breeze- a very nice day.
Extremes in temp above 90 degrees- weed growth turning brown.  Above average rainfall.
Frost or freezing temps 3 days in a row- 2" of snow on 9/22/95- partly sunny- slight SW wind temp at 10: 00- 45 degrees.
Ice-off 4/27/96- 10 days later than normal.  113" of snow.  Today's temp is 62 degrees- sunshine and calm.
Weed growth at max.  Algae levels in bays are high.  Partly cloudy- temp is 67 degrees- average rainfall for past 30 days is 3.5".
Near normal temp and rainfall- 70 degrees at 10 am.  Sunny with slight NW wind.  No secchi measurement on field sheet.
No killing frost yet- temp is 62 degrees- mostly sunny- wind moderate from the w.  Above normal precipitation for September
Two days prior to sample temperatures in the 90s.  74 degrees at time of sampling. large amount of Mayflies on 6/19-6/20.  Rain gauge reading from 6/1 to 6/25 = 7.25 inches.

Weed growth at maximum in bays.  Large amount of boat traffic- skiers- jet skis have eliminated weeds in some areas of the lake.  Very hot- humid days prior to sample.  Rain gauge reading from 6/25 to 7/15 = 3.5 inches.
No rainfall in last 15 days.  Lake still at normal level. temperature for the last five days 5 degrees below normal.  Temperature at sample time 58 degrees F.
1/2" rain since 4/5/98.  Ice off 4/3/98 earliest on record.
Water temp below normal- partly sunny- 2.5" rain 3/20 to 5/07- ice off 4/03.
6.5" rain since 5/11- minimal boat traffic last 30 days- today clear- sunny- 70 F.
Partly cloudy- water and air 76 F- 2.5" rain since 6/21- beautiful weather last 2 weeks.
Sunny- calm- and there is lake bloom.
Sunshine- still water- algae visible top of water- and there was 6.5" of rain since 7/19.
Sunshine- still water- algae visible on top of water- 3 1/2" rain since 8/25.
Ice out 3/20- earliest on record.  Rainfall below normal. partly sunny with SW wind.
6 1/2" rain since last sample.  Sunny- moderate NW wind. temperature averaging below normal.
Sunny- calm- and lots of algae.
Bright sunshine- no wind.  4" rain September- 0" in October. no boat traffic. 45 degrees F.
Ice out on 4/18/01.  Loons on the lake as ice is fading- southwest wind- partly cloudy- and color chart perception is 8.
4th day of rain on and off. Cloudy and breezy
Cloudy and light breeze. Rained in the morning
Above average rain- below normal temperatures- southwest wind at 5 mph- and the color chart perception is 7.
Hazy sun and clouds. Light breeze
Below average rainfall- rained on 7/17/01 0.5" and 0.4" on 7/08/01- southeast wind at 3 mph- the temperature is 77 degrees- and the color chart is number 7.
Hazy thin clouds. Nice wind and chop
Sunny and hot with light breeze
Sunny and hot with light breeze
Many dead snails washed up on shore- southwest wind at 10 mph- and the color chart is 8.
Clear blue sky and no wind. Lake flat
Leaves 60% changed- one loon on the lake- did see 10-15 mph wind on the lake in mid September- and the color chart is 6.
NW wind @5-10mph- cloudy + cool- Ice out 3 weeks ago- wet+cool spring- 7 on the color chart
Partly sunny- SW winds 1-3- warm day
Mostly cloudy E winds@ 2 miles an hour- finally some warm weather
SE winds@ 1-3- partly sunny- weeds are slow
West winds @ 10-12mph- sunny - windy and cloudy all week!
S winds @ 3-5 miles an hour- cloudy- it's been tough to get a sample the last two weeks - rainy + windy
North wind @ 1-3 miles per hour heavy boat traffic.
East wind @ 3-5 miles per hour- cloudy- 3 inches of rain on Sunday
Sunny SW winds @ 5-10 miles an hour- lake is in full bloom!
Sunny- SE winds @ 1-3- almost 4inches of rain over the weekend
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 2-3 miles an hour- lake is Brown + green- like pea soup!
We seem to have a outbreak of Blue Green Algae- pretty nasty along shores and back bays. Sunny and calm.
Partly cloudy- NE winds @ 3-6 miles an hour.
SW winds @ 5-10 miles an hour- partly sunny.
South winds @ 5-8 miles an hour- partly sunny.

Sunny- no clouds- and small waves.
Cool temps- cloudy- N winds @ 3-5- Lots of boat

column1: traffic over the weekend- Weeds are up.  Color chart percetion 7.

NE@5-8 miles an hour- partly sunny.  The weather has

column1: been quiet so far this summer.  The best Secchi depth reading that I can

column2: Bright sun and medium wind and waves
Overcast and windy with some rain
Has been cool (27 degrees below normal for last week).  Warming this week.  Dry summer. Sunny- calm.
Ice out 4/14/2004.  Bright sun + light breeze.
Sunny- West wind @ 5-7 mph.  The Spring has been cool and somewhat dry.  Three eagles on the lake.  Color chart comparison is a 7.
72 degrees- sunny and Calm- weather has been cool and wet.  Lots of snails in the lake- water seems clearer. Color chart 8.
Partly cloud; winds SW 3-5mph; July has been dry- lots of boat traffic this past weekend; the color chart would be a #9
Sunny + light breeze- lakes in bloom
Partly cloudy; southwest winds 3-5 mph.  August has been wet and cool.  Color chart:  8
Sunny; mild winds; good water clarity; warm fall; color chart close to #6
Ice out April 10th; partly cloudy; winds at SW 2-3 mph; last three weeks have been cool and wet.  Color chart #7
Cloudy- SW winds at 3 mph- weather has been warm- weeds are coming up fast.  Water temperature is 10 degrees warmer than this time last year.  Color chart perception:  7
Sunny; SW winds 5-6 mph; lot of boat traffic this past week; no rain for 10 days.  Water temperature is higher than normal; color chart perception is 7.
clear- sunshine- hot and light breeze
Winds SW 1-3mph; sunny; not much rain; water has been warm in July; also a huge snail die-off occurred in July.
West winds @10-15mph; sunny; lots of rain the last two weeks (over 9").
Ice out 4/11/06; SE winds 5-10mph; cloudy; very dry April; color chart perception is 9
overcast- light rain and medium chop
NW@5-7mph-cloudy- June has been very dry and windy.  Considerable weed growth along shore lines (mild winter)
N to NE winds 2-3 mph; partly cloudy; 1 inch of rain on Saturday; weeds are up big time on the lake; color chart perception is 7
mostly sunny and medium wind after 4 days of rain

NW @ 5 miles an hour- sunny.  Finally had seven inches of rain in two days at the beginning of the month.  A lot of green stuff was flushed into the lake.  Weeds are as bad as I can remember on Soo lake- not good for much shoreline activity.  Color Chart Comparison 7.
SE winds 5 mph; sunny; most all leaves are off the trees; fall came a week early.
Partly cloudy; NE winds 5-7 mph; ice out on April 2nd; very little snow this winter but had very deep ice.
Cool- partly cloudy- NE winds 3-5 mph; no rain in the past week.
Partly Cloudy - Sunny. Dense clouds. Loons- mallards. Bob Eastlick was my helper.
Partly cloudy - Sunny. Very windy with lots of current in the water. Lots of baby mallards.
PT/ Cloudy/Sunny - Many fisherman. Baby Mallards have hatched. The Goose population is less than last year. Eagles are doing well. Othere than that a beautiful day.
More mallard babys. Not as many geese.
S-SW winds at 10-15mph; party sunny; water clarity is excellent; weeds are running rampant; we are having a long stretch of very little rain.
The past few days we are finally getting some rain. Not much but anything helps.
Very windy- storms coming from the northwest. On and off rain
Winds calm; partly cloudy; weeds are taking over the lake; Eurasian milfoil is running rampant.
Water levels- like many area lakes is very low. The water is murky at best and the weeds are at an all time high. Didn't see any waterfowl of any type.
Sunny- SE winds @ 5-10 mph; it has been very dry- very little rain and the lake level has been dropping a 1/2 inch a day.  Weeds are in bloom everywhere.  Big areas of Eurasian Milfoil are spotted.
Water is very clear. Leaves are already at their full colors

Cloudy- SE winds 5-10 mph; Eurasian milfoil is running rampant on the lake; finally some rain the past couple of weeks to the tune of 8+ inches; the brown stain is a little more prevalent from the run off.
Sunny; NE winds 3-5 mph; good snow and very cold this winter and the color chart perception is a 7. Sunny; NE winds 3-5 mph; good snow; lot of runoff; very cold winter; color perception is a 7.

column1: Sunny; winds 3-5 mph out of the Northeast; ice out 4/23/08; a lot of snow and cold this winter.  Color chart perception is a 7.

column2: Partly sunny windsout of the NE@5-7.  We are getting more rain this year.  Water clarity is back to our normal range due to the runoff.  The main problem on the lake is the Eurasian Watermilfoil is coming up all-over in the main body of the lake.  There are some dense patches now forming where it would be impossible to motor through without clearing your motor.
Cloudy and wind is calm- people are starting to complain about EWM on the lake.

column1: It continues to spread- Craig Roessler is coming out in August to make an assessment of our situation.  Color chart preception is a 7.

column2: Sunny- winds out of the WNW @ 3-5- once again we could use some rain.  Water clarity is on the rise. EWM wide spread on the lake.
SW winds @ 3 miles an hour and sunny
Partly sunny- winds @ 5-7 from the SE.  Weather is cooling off in the 60"s. Winds out of the North at 3 miles an hour.  Pleasant fall day seeing flocks of geese

column1: over head. Winds out of the N @ 3 miles an hour.- sunny- pleasent fall day. N @ 3 miles an hour- pleasent fall day

column2: Winds NE 3 mph; pleasant fall day
Winds SE 5-7 mph; sunny- cool day; many geese overhead
Winds calm; sunny; 1.2 inches of rain Monday night
Winds E-SE 3-5 mph; partly cloudy; hard frost 10/4/08; still many migrating geese
Partly cloudy; NE wind 5-10 mph; very dry early spring; not much runoff from the watershed; water very clear for this time of the year.
SE wind @ 3-5- sunny and cool.  Finally- had some rain over the weekend- over an inch.
Calm; sunny; perfect spring day; opening weekend of fishing; evidence of a lot of EWM washed up on shore; presently the EWM is below the surface.  Color chart perception would be a 7.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the west @ 5-10- cool.  We have had rain cool temperatures and windy conditions.  Weeds are coming up quick.
Wind out of the NW@ 5-7- partly cloudy and cool.  The Eurasian milfoil is breaking out all over the lake.  It is very difficult to motor or fish in this weed.
SW winds @ 3-5 miles an hour- partly cloudy.  Finally some rain this past weekend- almost 2 inches.  We still are way below normal rainfall levels.

column1: EWM is everywhere- it is taking over the lake.

column2: Winds out of the SE @ 1-3- cloudy.  Finally in the 70's- very cool spring.  EWM all over the lake- boats are cutting it up.  Not a pretty picture- plus we have a fish kill on the lake- mostly Bluegils and a few Crappies.  I talked to Jeff Scheier- fish biologist out of Park Falls.  He believes it is Columnaries- the right set of circumstance have  occurred.  Water temps in the 65-70 degree range- some recent rain and fish spawning can set off this process- columnaries (bacteria from run-off) will kill the fish that are stressed out from spawning.   Many lakes in the northern basin are reporting fish kills.  No reason to be concerned unless we see massive amounts of dead fish.

SE winds @ 5-7- cloudy.  Not only do we have a lot of chopped EWM floating around we have a lot of dead Bluegils and some crappies.  Talked to Jeff Scheirer- fish biologist for the DNR working out of Park Falls.  He thought it was columnaries- a bacteria that effects the fish if they are in a stressed condition (like spawning).  They can die in 24 hours- but this was happening in lakes in the entire basin.  He claims it is quite common- but I haven't seen one this bad.
NW @ 3-5- partly cloudy- weeds getting worst.

WNW @ 7-10- sunny- nice day.  A lot of boat traffic over the Fourth of July- raked 7 wheel barrels of EWM out of the lake on Sunday.  It has exploded and we just are in July. WNW @ 7-10- sunny- nice day.  A lot of boat traffic over the Fourth of July- raked 7 wheel barrels of EWM out of the lake on Sunday.  It has exploded and we just are in July. WNW @ 7-10- sunny- nice day.  A lot of boat traffic over the Fourth of July- raked 7 wheel barrels of EWM out of the lake on Sunday.  It has exploded and we just are in July.
Cloudy- winds out of the SE @ 7-10.  The summer continues to be very dry and on the cooler side.
Partly cloudy- winds calm beautiful day.  The weather has been overcast- cool and dry this past week.  EWM weed is making boat traffic diffuclt.
Winds @ 3-5 out of WNW- partly sunny.  Soo lake is in the middle of an algae bloom.  The water looks yellow/green.  Saw 5 Loons on the lake.
Winds out of West @ 3-5- sunny.  The lake is in a bloom the water looks like pea soup.  Lots of dead snails floating in  the water- that has happened several times this summer.
Partly sunny- wind out of the WNW @3-5.  Algae bloom still in full bloom- lots of dead snails.
Sunny; South wind 3-5 mph; we are in the middle of an algae bloom; lots of cut-up EWM along the shoreline.  Water column temperature the same; 20-25 mph wind yesterday mixed the water well.
Sunny- winds out of the West @ 3-5.  Finally have been getting some rain.  The water is cclearing up after the algae bloom.
Sunny and winds are calm.  The evenings have been cool.  Watewr is clearing up- EWM terrible.
Sunny and winds are calm- not much boat traffic.  EWM makes fishing and boating difficult.
Winds calm- mostly sunny- warm day.  The last 10 days have been warmer than usual.  Boat traffic has been down partly becasue of the weeds.
Cloudy- winds out of the SE @ 3-5.  It has been warmer than normal for this time of year and no rain for a couple of weeks.  Water is low and boat traffic has been light.
Sunny- cool winds calm.  First hard freeze last night- temperature was 25 degrees this morning.
Cloudy and cool- winds out of the North @ 4-5.
Last reading of the year.  Partly cloudy- winds calm- temperature at 38.  Snow yesterday still traces on the ground- cooler than normal.
Cloudy- SW @ 5-10- ice out on March 30th.  Run-off was quick- a lot of EWM pulled up when ice started to move.  Lake is coming to life.
Winds out of the SSW @ 5-8.  Ice out was on March 30th.   Brisk morning with mostly sunny skies.
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 3 miles an hour.  April 20th and it is 71 degrees outside.  Starting to snag EWM when casting.
Sunny- winds @5-10 from the north.  Brisk sunny day- EWM just below the surface.  Lot's of water fowl on the lake.
Winds out of the SW @ 5-7- partly cloudy.
Calm wind- sunny day in the high 70's.  The lake looks beautiful- but the EWM is coming up big time.
Bright- sunny day- winds out of the South at 5-10.  EWM has taken over the lake and is becoming a big problem for any kind of boating.
Mostly sunny- wins out of the South@3-5 miles an hour.  The lake is a mess- cut up EWM floating everywhere.  It's going to be a long summer.
Cloudy- NW winds @ 3-5- water is darker we have had rain 11 out of the last 14 days.

Winds out of the WSW @ 5-8 miles an hour.  Water clarity has decreased the last couple of weeks.  We have been getting more rain- so more run off and back to the Brown stained water.  EWM out of control!
Brown stain is back in the water- over 4"s of rain last week.  Lake was very high and we had a lot of run off from the swamps.  Bays are really choked up with weeds.
NW winds @ 3-5- sunny beautiful evening.  14" of rain in June- dark brown stain in the water from all the run-off from the swamps.  EWM is out of control- tough to fish or boat.
Beautiful evening winds out of the WNW @ 1-3- sunny.  Algae bloom- water is somewhat green.
Beautiful evening- partly sunny winds out of the SE@5 miles an hour.  Lot EWM on top of the water.
Partly sunny- winds calm- beautiful day. Water is dark brown from all the run-off from the wet lands.  18"s of rain since the beginning of June.  Boat traffic light because of all the EWM.

Winds out of the SW @ 5-7- partly cloudy- great day.  EWM has really cut boat traffic down this summer.  Lot of cut up weeds floating into shore.  Water remains dark brown- loy of run off from the swamps.
NW wind @ 5-7- great day.  Lot of cut up EWM and floating weeds on surface.  Boat traffic is way down because of the condition of the lake.

WNW winds @ 10-15- mostly sunny.  Rain fall way above normal and it has been hot an humid.  Water temerature have dropped some- we have finally had a couple of cool evenings.  Water is dark brown from all the run-off.  Weeds (EWM) continue to make boating tough.
Last data entery for Soo Lake this year- draw down begins on Tuesday.  Sunny- wind calm- great day.
Very cold and wet April- due to the draw down on Soo lake this winter this was the first chance to get a sample.  Cool- cloudy with winds out of the WNW at 5-10.

column1: Lot of floating wood- water is back to a dark brown stain from all the run off.

column2: Partly sunny- humid day- winds out of the north @ 1-3.  Spring has been wet and cool.
Sunny- winds out of the north @ 3-5.
Sunny- mild day- winds out of the North @ 3-5.  Did pull up a few strands of what I believe is EWM.  Next few weeks will determine how the drawdown affected the EWM.
Partly sunny- winds out of the SW@1-3.  Extremely windy the last two days- a lot of debris floating in the water.  Logs washed up on to the shore- the water looks murky.
Partly sunny winds out of tHe NE at 5-10.  We have hit a dry spell with temperatures in the 90's- but dropped into the 60;s today.
Sunny- winds out of the SE @ 1-3.  Great Day to be on the water.  Some EWM is appearing- but scattered.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the ESE @ 3-5.  We have had rain and forecasting rain all week.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the WNW @ 5-7.
Mostly sunny- winds are calm- beautiful day.  A lot of boat traffic over the fourth of July weekend.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the West @1-3- great day.
Weather is hot and humid- water seems cloudy.
Sunny a light wind out of the SW at 1-3.
Sunny and calm winds- had 3 1/2" of rain over the weekend.
Partly cloudy- wind out of the WNW @ 3-5.  Temperature in the 70's- greay day to be on the water.
Sunny- winds out of the WSS @ 5-7.
Sunny and windy. 10-15 miles per houir out of the West.
Cloudy- winds out of the  SE @ 3-5iles an hour.
Cool- partly cloudy- winds ouy of the WNW @ 5-10
Wind out of the WNW @ 5-10- sunny and cool in the 60's.  Water claraity has increased in the last two weeks- we have had some cold nights.
Cloudy- winds calm- the weather has been rainy all week.  The trees are turning colors at a rapid pace.
Partly sunny- wnds out of the SE at 5-10.  This will be the last report of the season.
Sunny- winds out of the NNW @ 10-13.  Ice went out exactly two weeks ago- March 19th.  One of the earliest times I can remember.
Mostlly cloudy- winds outr of the N@5-7.  Weather has been more seasonal after a early warm spell.  Hard nto get a sunny day.
Winds out of the SE @ 10-12- mostly sunny.  Weather has been windy and cool- first sunny day that we have had in a while.
West wind @ 8 to 12- mostly sunny.  We had almost an inch of rain yesterday.
Sunny- winds out of the WNW @ 5-7
Sunny NE wind @ 3 miles an hour.  1" of rain yesterday. beautiful today.
Cloudy- wind out of the North 1-3 miles an hour.  Water is darker because of all the run-off of recent rains.
Sunny- winds out of the NW @ 10 to 15 mph.  No rain in ten days- lake looks good.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the SW @ 1-3.  Last few days we have had a couple inches of rain.  It was much needed.
Sunny- winds out of the WNW @ 5-7 miles an hour.
Hot- sunny day outside tempertaure is 94 degrees.  Wind out of the W @ 3-5- some algae bloom.
Sunny winds out of the SW @ 3-5.
Sunny and warm- winds out of SW @ 10-15.  Algae bloom is bad- the weather has been warm and very little rain in the last two weeks.
Sunny- winds out of the West @ 3-5.  Surface water temp was 84.  It has been very warm with moderate rainfall.
Sunny- winds out of the West @ 3 miles an hour.  Weather remains warm- water temps are in the mid 80"s- algae bloom in full swing.
Mostly sunny winds out of the NE@1-3.  We have had some cool nights- the algea seems to be knocked down some.
Winds out of the West @ 3 miles an hour- partly sunny.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the North @ 3-5- nice mild temperature day.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the North @ 1-3 miles an hour.
Sunny- winds out of the West @ 3-5 miles an hour.
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 10-15.
Cloudy and cool- winds out of the N @ 3-5 miles an hour.
Sunny- winds out of the North at 3-5.
Sunny. mild day winds ouit of the North @ 3-5 miles an hour.  The trees are 80% color- great day to be on the lake  Weeds are dying back.

Cool sunny day- winds out of the SW @ 5-7.  Ice out was on 05/02/2013- water is still high because of all the snow run-off.  All kinds of water fowl have stopped in on Soo lake this Spring- including swans.
Mostly sunny- wind out of the SW @ 5-7.  Delightful day to be on the lake.
Winds SE at 10- front moving in from the south- hazy skies prior to storm- had just caught a 14-15 inch smallmouth
Sunny- winds out of the NE @ 3-5- water still dark- still a lot of run-off from the swamp.
Light SE wind- overcast skies- post large overnight rain storm- more rain on the way- Bob Mayer helper
winds 5-10 SSE- partly cloudy turning mostly cloudy
Strong SW winds- Clear and warm day- Lots of boat traffic- mid 70 degree water temps
strong SE wind- whitecaps on water- 79 degree surface temps- two ducks trying to cross lake Strong SE wind- whitecaps on water- clear skies- 79 degree surface temps- two ducks trying to cross lake
Partly sunny- winds out of the SW @ 5-7.  Weed growth has really picked up this month- we are finding some EWM.
Clearing skies- light haze- storms to the North- winds 5-10 from the South- 80 degree surface temps- just caught a 38 inch musky- 3 loons in middle of lake about an hour earlier
mostly sunny- winds 5-10 out of the north- seagull sitting right on top of deep hole when I came up
light variable wind- partly cloudy- some storm clouds in area- light algae bloom on lake- heavier in shoreline areas
cloudy- light rain in area- had rained overnight- light SSE wind- lake still in algae bloom but lighter than last test- many loons on lake more than usual
5 mph west wind- algae bloom (heavier on shoreline)- many loons still on lake- lots of boat traffic this weekend- assisted by Bob Mayer
8-10 mph west wind- partly cloudy- no boat traffic today- mid to upper 30's overnight- some algae still on lake mostly in bays and shorlines
Winds out of the SW @ 8-12 mph- mostly sunny.  A blue green algae bloom is taking place.
clear skies- 5-10 NW wind- lots of rain yesterday evening- highs in upper 70's today
north wind 10-12 mph- mostly cloudy- big rain fell overnight- high water- lots of flow coming in the Elk River
Sunny- calm day.  4-5 "s of rain Friday.  It has been a cool- wet spring.  The winter was cold and a lot of snow.
Weather has turned warm- winds are calm- we continue to get rain.  The Elk river has a steady current.
Beautiful summer day- winds out of the SE @ 3-5- mostly sunny.  We continue to have rain- the mosquitoes are the worst I've seen in years.
Mostly sunny; winds 12-15 mph out of the SW; weather continues to be wet and mosquitoes are out of control
Winds out of the NW@3-5- partly cloudy.
caught northern pike moments before reading
Winds out of the NE @ 5-7 miles an hour- partly cloudy.
caught 2 smallies- one before reading- one after. Overcast (light). Light wind
Mostly sunny- winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Weeds are coming up quickly- late start with a late spring and high water.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the NW @ 5-7 miles an hour.  Water appears to be much darker- weeds are coming up quickly.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the SSW @ 7 miles an hour.  Weeds are coming up after a slow start.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the NE @ 3-5 miles an hour.
caught 42in musky at 9:05am day of reading. Sunny- light wind
Mostly sunny day- winds out of the WNW @ 1-2 miles an hour.
Sunny mild day- winds out of the NNW @ 7-10 miles an hour.  Loons have been active- there are five on the lake.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the SE @ 10-12.  Not much sun in the last 10 days.
caught 36in musky at 7:00 pm that evening of reading. Nice weather- clear and light wind
Mostly sunny- winds out of the SE @ 3-5.  5 inches of rain the last two day- seems like a short summer.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the WSW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Lot of rain and a lot of run-off the last couple of weeks.
Sunny- mild day- winds out  of the S at 3-5.  Water remains dark from all the run off.  Colors are at 60%- we could be at peak colors by next week.  Summer has been way to short this year.
SE wind a 7 to 12 mph- some chop. brief light rain an hour or so prior to reading. Mostly cloudy
3 days of clear unseasonable warm weather. Clear with light south wind
Sunny- wind out of the SSW @ 10-15 miles an hour
Sunny- bright- cool spring day.  Winds out of the NNW @ 7-10 miles an hour.   Sunny- bright day- winds out of the NNW @ 7 -10 miles an hour.
mostly clear day- felt very "early season"
Beautiful opening day weather- temps are in the low 70's.  Mostly sunny- winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.
Sunny- evening- winds out of the ESE @ 3-5.
Beautiful Spring day- sunny winds out of the SSE @ 3-5.
Opening day musky!! Lake crowed- overcast- light chop
10 to 15 Knots with medium chop on water. clear skies- small musky caught at 4pm.  10 to 15 Knots with medium chop on water. clear skies- small musky caught at 4pm. 69 degree surface temps
Sunny- winds out of the WNW @ 2 to 3 miles an hour.  It has been raining quite a bit- hard to find the sun.  Noticed some EWM growth.
Sunny- winds are calm- beautiful summer day.  Fair amount of rain the last couple of weeks. Weed growth is evident and their is some EWM present.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the N@2-3 miles an hour.  Weeds growth has really taken off this past week.
Choppy- 15-18 knots wind- partly cloudy. Very busy on the water today- lots of boat traffic with the Holiday week. 68.2 degree surface temps
Partly cloudy- winds out of the SSW @ 8 miles an hour.  Lots of boat traffic on the lake this past weekend (4th of July).
Partly cloudy- winds out of the west @ 5-8 miles an hour.  Partly cloudy- winds out of the West @ 5-8 miles an hour.  There is a algae bloom taking place on the lake right now.
Partly sunny- winds out of the West @ 10 to 15 miles an hour.
Very windy day on the lake- with small storms systems moving out at time of reading. Some boat traffic- mostly pleasure boaters. Slow fishing
calm winds- mostly clear skies. little boot traffic. two loons and one eagle moving around main lake basin at time of reading.
10-15 mph wind out of the NW- mostly sunny. little boat traffic
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 7-10miles an hour.
clear- warm with lots of small bait fish breaking surface throughout "deep hole"
Partly sunny- winds out of the SW @# 10-15 miles an hour.
Partly cloudy- muggy and winds out of the South @ 5-7miles an hour.
Winds out of the NW @ 5-7 miles an hour- sunny and cool.
Partly sunny- winds out of the N @ 3-5 miles an hour.
Sunny- cool a great fall day.  Winds out of the N@5-7 miles an hour.
Sunny- fall day- winds out of the E@1-3 mph.
Cloudy day winds out of the SE @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Loons- geese and ducks are back- also some water fowl that have stopped for a rest.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the NNE @ 5-7miles an hour.
Cool and partly sunny- winds out of the NE at 7-12 miles an hour.
Sunny- winds out of the NE at 5-7.  It has been an early spring- but cool.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the South @ 5-7.  It has been dry- but we are heading into a rainy period.
Sonny- winds out of the WSW @ 7-12 miles an hour.  4"s of rain over the last 5 Days.
Mild sunny day- wind is calm.  Seeing more signs of EWM.
Sunny- winds calm- great day.  We continue to have rain- the last two or three weeks have been wet.  Saw the loons with their baby chick.  EWM keeps showing up around the lake.
Sunny- mild evening- winds where calm.  Weeds are coming up fast.
Cloudy- winds out of WNW @ 6 miles an hour.  5" of rain Saturday night- lake is high.  Last 3 weeks have been rainy- weeds are coming up big time.
Cloudy- winds out of the SE @ 5-8.

Partly cloudy- winds out of WNW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Weeds are up big time- not just EWM. Partly cloudy- winds out of the WNW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Weeds are starting to choke off some of the back bays.
Sunny- winds out of the South @6-8 miles an hour.
Mostly sunny winds out of the SW- water clarity is down.  I suspect because of all the run off from the woods and swamps.
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 1-3 miles an hour.  We are in the dog days of summer- weeds everywhere.
Wind was calm- sunny day- weeds out of control.
Sunny with winds out of the SW @10-15 miles an hour.  The weeds are out of control in the shallow bays.
Cool day- mostly sunny winds out of the SW @ 10-12 miles an hour.  Seems like the geese have already left Soo lake.
Sunny- cool day winds are calm.  Water level has been up and down with all the rain- a lot of runoff from the swamps.  Sited the two baby loons yesterday- glad to see both of them made the summer-
Cloudy- winds out of the NE@5-7 miles an hour.  Another 3 and 1/2 "s of rain last night- lake remains a dark brown color.
Partly sunny- winds out of the NE @ 7-10.  Water clarity remains low for this time of year- probably because of all the run-off of the swamps with all the rain we have had this fall.
Sunny SE winds @ 3-5miles an hour.  This is the last Seechi test for the year- boat comes out this weekend. Sunny- winds out of the SE @ 3-5.
Sunny- cool day- slight wind out of the North.  Geese- some ducks and a few swans were spotted on the lake.
Partly sunny- winds out of the SE @ 5-7.  Weather has been up and down- hard to find a sunny day.  Loons and geese are back. Partly sunny- winds out of the SE @ 5-7 miles an hour.
Partly cloudy winds out of the SW @ 5-7 miles an hour.  It is been hard to find a sunny day to take a reading- it has been cool and wet.
Sunny- mild day- winds out of the NE @ 3-5.  It has been a very wet April- water level has been high.
Wind was calm on a partly cloudy day and the temperature was in the 70's.  We continue to have rain- water level has been high and a lot of drain off from the swamps.
Sun and light winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Weeds and EWM are on the rise.  I suspect the EWM will be  a problem this summer due to the early ice out.
Sunny dat- winds out of the NE @ 3-5- great day to be on the water.  Weeds are coming up fast- ducks and geese are showing off their brood.

Partly sunny- winds out of the WNW @n10-15 miles an hour.  Tough to find a day without rain- the lake is higher than normal.  Earlier in the week we had 5 1/2 or rain and another 1 1/2 last night.  EMW and weeds are coming up quick.
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 5-10 miles an hour.  Lots of boat traffic over the 4th- water clarity is down.  Weeds are growing at a rapid rate- early ice off didn't help.
Sunny- calm evening- we continue to get rain.  The lake has settled down from the fourth- but the weeds are popping up all over.
Sunny with winds out of the NNE @ 7-10 miles an hour.
Mostly sunny- winds calm.  Severe out break of algae evident.
Mostly sunny- winds calm- weed growth exploding.  Blue green algea evident through out the lake.
NW winds at 3-5 miles an hour- sunny and cool.

Mostly cloudy with winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Water temperatures have gone down 12 degrees from last month- we have had rain and cooler temperatures especially at night. Mostly cloudy with winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Water temperatures have gone down 12 degrees from last month- we have had rain and cooler temperatures especially at night. Mostly cloudy with winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Water temperatures have gone down 12 degrees from last month- we have had rain and cooler temperatures especially at night.
We went from winter to summer- not much of a spring.   Winds out of the NW @ 3-5- mostly sunny and warm.  After the snow melt- it has been dry.
Sunny- winds out of the West @ 10 miles an hour- we finally got some rain this past week.
Sunny- winds out of the SE @ 8-10 miles an hour.  2 1/2" rain last night.  Weeds are starting to come up on the lake.
Sunny day winds out of the NE @ 10-15 miles an hour.  We had up to 10"s of rain last week- we where in flood conditions.  Water clarity was down- a lot of swamp run off.
Sunny warm day- winds out of the SW@5-10 miles an hour.  The lake level has finally returned to normal pool level.
Sunny- light winds- a lot of boat traffic all week.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the NE@ 3-5 miles an hour.  Water temp has come down some- we have had some cooler weather.  Weeds have taken off. lots of boat traffic.
Warm- sunny day- winds out of the W @3-4 miles an hour.  A lot of pike weeds around the lake.
Mostly sunny- winds out of the West @ 1-3 miles an hour.
Light winds- haze in the sky from smoke from fires in the west.  Water remains warm fueling the growth of weeds.
Sunny- winds out of the SW @ 10-15 miles an hour.
Partly cloudy- winds out of the SW @15-20 miles an hour.  Water temps are going down- nights have been cooler.
Sunny- winds out of the NE @ 3-5 miles an hour.

Partly cloudy- winds out of the ENE @ 2-3 miles an hour.  Ice went off on 04/28/2019.  20 to 30 loons on the lake feeding on bait fish- ducks and geese also sighted on the lake.  Like usual Lac Sault Dore was the first lake in the area to have it's ice off.  11 days ahead of last year.
Sunny day- light winds out of the W@ 2-3 miles an hour.  Saw an eagle and heard the geese.
Lake levels have been up and down- we have had a lot of rain.
Mostly sunny- wind out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Weeds are growing- seems like they are behind normal years.  Probably do to the cold and wet weather we had this Spring.

Overcast day- winds out of the SE @ 5-7 miles an hour.  Not the best day to do a test- but rain is in the forecast all week.  I needed to grab a water sample before the end of the month. Overcast day- winds out of the SE @ 5-7 miles an hour.  Not the best day to do a test- but rain is in the forecast all week.  I needed to grab a water sample before the end of the month.
Light winds out of the SW- mostly sunny humid day.  Traffic on the lake has picked up because of the upcoming holiday.
light winds- warm and humid.  Weeds are growing at a fast rate.
Sunny skies- wind out of the WNW @ 5-7 miles an hour.  Weeds have taken over on many shorelines.  The Loons have been observed with two chicks in tow.
Sunny and warm-  surface water temperatures 79 degrees.  Weeds are every where not pleasant for swimming.
Cool summer evening- sunny with winds out of the North @ 3-5 miles an hour.  Over 5"s of rain this past week.
Mostly cloudy- winds out of the SE @ 8 10 miles an hour.  Some leafs are starting to change around the lake.
weather pattern has been wet and windy
Cloudy with a SW wind @ 3-5 miles an hour.
Sunny-winds out of the WNW @ 10 - 15 miles an hour.
Cool- overcast day- SW winds @ 12-15.  Ice off the lake on 04/09/2020-  a flock of Swans have been on the lake for a few days.
Sunny day- winds out of the SE@10-12 miles an hour
5 inches of rain last week- weeds are coming up.  SE wind @ 10 miles an hour.
Partly cloudy day- winds out of the WNW @ 4 miles an hour.  Almost 5"s of rain last week- thew weeds are really coming up.
Mostly sunny. winds out of the SW@ 5-7 miles an hour-  we have had rain on and off.  The weeds have taken off all over the lake.
Winds out of the WNW @ 10-15-  partly cloudy.  Lots of rain this week- the weeds have become dense in the lake.
Cloudy- warm and muggy- winds out of the SW @ 3-5 miles an hour.  The weeds in the lake are out of control.
